<i>adjective</i>: 서슴없다 [서스멉따] <i>adverb</i>: 흔쾌히 [흔쾌히], 흔연히 [흐년히], 툭하면 [투카면], 쾌히 [쾌히], 쉽사리 [쉽ː싸리], 쉬이 [쉬이], 소르르 [소르르], 성큼 [성큼], 선뜻 [선뜯], 걸핏하면 [걸피타면] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>adjective</i><br>
<dt>서슴없다 [서스멉따]</dt><br>
<dd>readily</dd><br>
<dd>말이나 행동에 망설임이나 막힘이 없다.</dd><br>
<dd>Not hesitating in one's remark or behavior.</dd><br>
</li>
<li><i>adverb</i><br>
<dt>흔쾌히 [흔쾌히]</dt><br>
<dd>happily; gladly; readily</dd><br>
<dd>기쁘고 유쾌하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of being happy and pleasant.</dd><br>
<dt>흔연히 [흐년히]</dt><br>
<dd>gladly; readily</dd><br>
<dd>기쁘고 반가워서 기분이 좋게.</dd><br>
<dd>Gladly and happily in a willing manner.</dd><br>
<dt>툭하면 [투카면]</dt><br>
<dd>easily; readily</dd><br>
<dd>조금이라도 일이나 기회가 있기만 하면 바로.</dd><br>
<dd>Immediately at the slightest provocation.</dd><br>
<dt>쾌히 [쾌히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. pleasantly</dd><br>
<dd>즐겁고 신이 나게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a happy and excited manner.</dd><br>
<dd>2. completely</dd><br>
<dd>앓던 질병이 다 나아 건강한 상태로.</dd><br>
<dd>In a healthy state after recovering from a disease.</dd><br>
<dd>3. readily; without hesitation</dd><br>
<dd>말과 행동이 머뭇거림 없이 시원하게.</dd><br>
<dd>Without hesitation in one's speech and action.</dd><br>
<dt>쉽사리 [쉽ː싸리]</dt><br>
<dd>readily; with ease</dd><br>
<dd>아무 탈이나 어려운 점 없이 아주 쉽게.</dd><br>
<dd>Very easily without any trouble or difficulty.</dd><br>
<dt>쉬이 [쉬이]</dt><br>
<dd>1. easily; readily</dd><br>
<dd>힘들거나 어렵지 않게.</dd><br>
<dd>Without trouble or difficulty.</dd><br>
<dd>2. easily</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일이 일어날 가능성이 많게.</dd><br>
<dd>With a high possibility that something will happen.</dd><br>
<dd>3. soon; before long</dd><br>
<dd>금방이나 길지 않은 시간 후에.</dd><br>
<dd>Shortly or after a short time.</dd><br>
<dt>소르르 [소르르]</dt><br>
<dd>1. smoothly; readily</dd><br>
<dd>얽히거나 뭉친 물건이 쉽게 잘 풀리는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing a tangled thing unwinding easily.</dd><br>
<dd>2. gently</dd><br>
<dd>바람이 천천히 부드럽게 불어오는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the wind blowing slowly and softly.</dd><br>
<dd>3. quietly</dd><br>
<dd>물이나 가루 등이 조용히 부드럽게 새어 나오는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing water, powder, etc., coming through something quietly and softly.</dd><br>
<dd>4. quietly</dd><br>
<dd>살며시 졸음이 오거나 잠이 드는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing one falling asleep or dozing off quietly.</dd><br>
<dt>성큼 [성큼]</dt><br>
<dd>1. in a big stride</dd><br>
<dd>다리를 높이 들어 크게 떼어 놓는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing one raising one's legs high and moving them in a big stride.</dd><br>
<dd>2. readily</dd><br>
<dd>동작이 망설임 없이 매우 시원스럽고 빠른 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing a gesture being brisk and quick without hesitation.</dd><br>
<dd>3. suddenly</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 때가 갑자기 가까워진 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing a certain time nearing suddenly.</dd><br>
<dt>선뜻 [선뜯]</dt><br>
<dd>readily; gladly; willingly</dd><br>
<dd>아무 망설임이나 어려움 없이 쉽게.</dd><br>
<dd>Promptly without hesitation or difficulties.</dd><br>
<dt>걸핏하면 [걸피타면]</dt><br>
<dd>easily; readily</dd><br>
<dd>무슨 일이 조금이라도 있기만 하면 바로.</dd><br>
<dd>Immediately at the slightest provocation.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>